<div id="map">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col p-3">
            <h2 id="map-head">SKREET MAP&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="#" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Location should be as close as possible, we want to know what side of the building the piece is on. Be specific! "><img src="/images/info.svg" ></a></h2>
              <input id="pac-input" class="controls" type="text" placeholder="Search Box">
                <div id="mapBox"></div>
       
         </div>
     </div>
     <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-6 p-3">
            <h2 class="mb-2">Upload Image</h2>
            <h6 class="text-muted">Browse your device</h6>

            <form action="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data" id="file">
                <input type="file" accept="image/*" name="photo" class="btn btn-outline-info">
                
                <button id="submit" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Submit</button>
                <h4 id="u-sure"></h4>
            </form>
            <br>
            <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" id="preview"
                style="max-width: 250px;">
            <br><br>
            <h4 id="result"></h4>

            <a href="/">‚Üê Back To Home</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="/gallery">Gallery</a>
                
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-6 p-3 pr-5">
          <h4>How it works:</h4>
          <p style="line-height: 1.6;">Drag and move the map to place a marker on the screen. Try to get your marker as close as possible to where the art is located, e.g, on the side of the building,
            not just the address. Once a marker is on the screen, that location has been captured. Don't worry though, if you need to change it, just
            pick a new spot! we only record the coordinates of the marker at the time you hit the submit button </p>
        </div>

      </div>
            
         
     </div>
</div>


